article.headline: Howard 13, Norfolk State 10
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Quarterback Brian Johnson rushed for a career-high 142 yards on 18 carries and Howard's defense registered six sacks in a 13-10 victory Saturday over Norfolk State. Howard (3-5, 2-3 MEAC) has now won consecutive games for the first time this season, while Norfolk State (3-5, 1-5 MEAC) dropped its fourth straight. Johnson led a group of four Howard rushers that outgained the Spartans on the ground, 275 yards to 63. They did it with a series of inside handoffs and quarterback keepers that wore down Norfolk State's defense. Howard led 3-0 when Johnson's 42-yard run on third down set up first-and-goal from Norfolk State's 10-yard line. Two plays later, Antoine Rutherford scampered five yards around the right end and dove inside the pylon for a touchdown that made the score 10-0 with 5:42 to play in the first half. Dennis Wiehberg made a 22-yard field goal in the third quarter that gave the Bison defense a sufficient cushion. Norfolk State trimmed the margin to three with 8:53 remaining on a 1-yard touchdown plunge by Daryl Jones on fourth down, but the Spartans turned the ball over on downs on their final possession. Howard yielded fewer than 20 points for the fifth straight game.
